result.adr_address: 16 Staunton St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Al Dente Soho

reviews.text: The food was really good, if you like eating cheap, but you get hungry with typical lunch serving size then place this place is the place for you.  My wife and I got the below with a great salad and very moist bread🤤. Definitely worth every penny of the lunchtime price!

The food was good, not the best but definitely not a disappointment. 
Vibe was the best part about the place! It's located in a quiet SOHO area right next to the Mid Levels escalators. 
The staff was very friendly and welcoming. Definitely worth a visit!
Great value, tasty food with generous portions. Swift and efficient table service. Everything a small restaurant should be and nothing it shouldn’t.

Stopped by for lunch and enjoyed the three-course fixed price lunch menu. Our salads were fresh and the dressing was light, providing just the right balance of flavour. Our steaks were done nicely. They came with colourful roasted vegetables, which still had a little crispness and bite. Lovely chocolate cake and ice cream for dessert. On the higher side price wise, but you get a lot. Service was attentive without being obtrusive. Perfect I would say.

I was blown away by the size of the portions. The food tasted amazing and I really enjoyed a full plate of food for once. 

The staff were incredibly friendly and quick to help. 

The atmosphere was quiet and cosy, while playing some opera or classical songs. A great place to have dinner with friends that you would enjoy talking to.
